<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-51-0258 </DOCNO><TEXT>Modern tomographic techniques, sonography, computed tomography and magneticresonance imaging have changed diagnostic possibilities tremendously.However, their indications overlap concerning different organs and regionsof the body. Nevertheless, there exists a precise spectrum of indicationsfor any individual diagnostic problem. Main subjects for ultrasound examinationsare abdomen, soft tissues of the extremities, and the cervical region.Computertomography completes the examination of retroperitoneal space,pelvis, thorax and mediastinum. Magnetic resonance becomes the methodeof choice for neuroradiology.</TEXT></DOC>